<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-298-167  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 298 167.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  Jan 23 1989 v10 n4 p13(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Optical storage waits for spotlight. (Comdex 1988)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Optical disk technologies made only an average showing at FallComdex 1988, according to a report by International Data Corp. Theexcitement of the new rewriteable products was diminished byearlier show appearances and the splashy introduction of the NeXTcomputer.andP;  The design of new microcomputer systems that includesoptical disk technology is happening slowly.andP;  Except for CD-ROMs,the current technology does not accommodate optical disk drivesvery efficiently.andP;  The absence of a consistent user interface isblamed for the lackluster sales of CD-ROM technology.andP;  Marketgrowth for the 5.25-inch WORM technology has been slow due to thelack of an emerging standard.andP;  The slower 12-inch WORM productshave found a niche within the computer storage hierarchy.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Optical MemoryCD-ROMWORMMarket Analysis5.25&quot; DiskDisk Storage.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   5.25&quot; WORM products. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>